  <dsc><c01 id="aspace_f71c445dc5dd3afa1cac2b449494adc4" level="series"><did><unittitle><extref xlink:href="http://rmc.library.cornell.edu/EAD/pdf_guides/RMM01550.pdf">Link to a partial finding aid.</extref></unittitle></did><scopecontent id="aspace_8044880be59dad3eddfa03dc8c9c697a"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>All the material in the collection may not be covered by this guide.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 audience="internal" id="aspace_057c9511bbdcce1c9ac95f400cb66cab" level="series"><did><unittitle>Series I. Records of John Greig</unittitle></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_f92777f40bdb32f3348b423b7d175fd1"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>John Greig Letters, Papers and Records 1794-1870 contained on 18 rolls microfilm (positive) and 18 rolls (negative).  The microfilm copies (11 1/2 rolls) of the papers of John Greig (b. 1779 - d. 1858), a Canandaigua lawyer, land agent and speculator, prominent in the economic development of western New York, relating to his activities as land agent and land owner, to his other business activities, to his role as an internal improvements promoter, to the settlement of his estate, and to his family affairs; consist of letters from agents, clients, business associates, settlers, friends, and relatives; deeds, bonds, notes, contracts; tax receipts, surveys, powers of attorney; accounts of purchases, payments; unsold lands; and other papers.        (Accompanying these papers is an index - on 3 rolls microfilm).    (Index - donated by certain Cornell Alumni from Rochester, N.Y. Dec. 1954)  The Card Index is actually a fairly elaborate calendar to the papers, containing references to subjects, persons, places, firms, etc.  The Index is, of course, alphabetically arranged, but within a particular subject, for instance, the cards are arranged chronologically.</p></scopecontent><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_85ba59c88f83c8f167170aa7c7c9ed26" level="file"><did><unittitle>Folder 1 through Folder 30</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1803/1826" type="inclusive">1803-1826</unitdate><container id="aspace_f415b952440ded60c78a289737b7eef7" label="Mixed Materials" type="microfilm reel">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_54ca774444c11eb227f1dc9b21197d66"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Letters, papers and records of Thomas Morris - (1790-1848)</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_61db8f7ab31ec51b4c2af70d1de285ef" level="file"><did><unittitle>Card File Index for papers</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">date unknown</unitdate><container id="aspace_8f8ecf3aa24e0534dfb73997fb812ae2" label="Mixed Materials" type="microfilm reel">1</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_c07da6f0a1b97eed0b989b92c9b9c6a2"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Index for papers,  Abby - Jane Greig, Inc.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_9e31116e098161975b1db2c994584828" level="file"><did><unittitle>Folder 31  through Folder 57</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1826/1830" type="inclusive">1826-1830</unitdate><container id="aspace_a07c1fcc1132bb27c93b1549ea6c56cc" label="Mixed Materials" type="microfilm reel">2</container></did></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_8970afafe1458db875bfb9e114a6a9c8" level="file"><did><unittitle>Card File Index for papers</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">date unknown</unitdate><container id="aspace_383ac913c6f23a077b84f698c06dd642" label="Mixed Materials" type="microfilm reel">2</container></did><scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_a9e01939439d06a01b13c95d4925ffde"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Index for papers, John Greig:   Sy-Sy, Inc.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 audience="internal" id="aspace_e6109d3168034316b27f57258b358ea6" level="file"><did><unittitle>Folder 58 through Folder 82</unittitle><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1830/1835" type="inclusive"